com.github.restdriver.clientdriver

Class SecureClientDriverFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.restdriver.clientdriver.SecureClientDriverFactory

  • public class SecureClientDriverFactory
extends Object
    Factory to create a ClientDriver object which supports SSL. To arrange that a key store has to be provided. The required password has to be the password of the certificate's private key as well as of the key store. This is usually the case if the certificate is exported via OpenSSL e.g. as PKCS#12 format. An example to create a certificate with keytool provided in the JDK: 
      $ keytool -genkey -keyalg RSA -dname "cn=SecureClientDriver" \ 
  -alias certificate -keystore keystore.jks -keypass password \ 
  -storepass password -validity 360 -keysize 2048
